==English==
===Etymology===
From {{OE.}} {{term|scieran}}, from {{Ger.}} *{{term||skeran}}, from {{IE.}} *{{term||(s)ker-}}.  Cognate with Dutch {{term|scheren|lang=nl}}, German {{term|scheren|lang=de}}, Norwegian {{term|skjære}}, Swedish {{term|skära}}; and (''from Indo-European'') with Ancient Greek {{term|sc=Grek|κείρω|tr=keirō||I cut off}}, Latin {{term|caro||flesh}}, Lithuanian {{term|skìrti||separate}}, Welsh {{term|ysgar||separate}}.

